history.content: Can't say much about 126 and 106a (also planning to take it this fall) but 61C is much more enjoyable in the fall with Garcia so I would suggest switching (I took it with Weaver in the spring). Also from what I've heard 106a starts off slow but has a tedious project at the end. Your spring semester will definitely be much harder as I've heard that 106B has 2x the workload of 106a.

Hi, I am a rising senior graduating in fall 2020. I am planning to take EE126, CS 186, EE106A as well as doing a 10 hours/week commitment for undergraduate research. Is the workload manageable for a student whose focus is purely on academic without doing clubs, social life, etc. ?

Also, my plan for next semester would be CS189, CS61C, and EE106B, is it also doable with 10 hours/week commitment for research?

Should I switch CS 61C with CS186? Or, the schedule now is better?
history.subject: Courseload EE126 + CS 186 + EE106A Suggestion
